				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AA path<a name="19491"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 6 04 5:09 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Fading Memories =&gt; GET THIS ASAP!
<br />

<br />
Then, in no particular order:
<br />

<br />
MC1/2 if you don't have much FT
<br />
IM3
<br />
Extended notes (or whatever extends range on beneficial ae songs)
<br />
Boastful Bellow if you pull a lot
<br />

<br />
After those, I'd look at defensive AA:
<br />
ND3, CA3, CS1, PE, LR5, CS3.... ID5 somewhat debatable use.
<br />

<br />
Then other bard stuff like SM3, JF3, something like that, probably missed one or two. Once you got all those, dps stuff like HA and ambidex perhaps.
<br />

<br />
Note I'm only 56 so not talking from personal experiance but this is roughly my game plan, there's no &quot;Best&quot; path although I think all will agree to get FM asap. All depends on your play style, typical song line ups, role in raids, equipment etc etc.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
