			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AA path<a name="38423"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 5 04 4:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If I was level 65 with 0 AAs, this would be the exact AA path I would persue.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Fade
<br />
Run 3
<br />
Regen 3
<br />
Natural Durability 3
<br />
Combat Agility 3
<br />
Combat Fury 1
<br />
Boastful Bellow
<br />
Instrument &amp; Singing Mastery 3
<br />
Jam Fest 3
<br />
Extended Notes 3
<br />
Lightning Reflexes 5
<br />
Physical Enhancement
<br />
Improved Instrument Mastery
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
One thing to keep in mind is if you're going to ba primarily a raiding bard, you absolutely <b>NEED</b> to get Jam Fest 3.
<br />
Stacking issues are such that virtually all of your songs (AE Resists, Marr, HOS, Slow, Mez) will be overwritten by any other bard on the raid that has a higher JF than you.
<br />

<br />
Mana regen and CA/LR and Mana regen is less important tertiary bards on a raid as you wont often be required or expected to pull.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
